Pre-K Enrollment 07/22/20
This is a message for any parents needing to enroll your child in Pre-K for this fall. Whether you completed our pre-enrollment questionnaire online earlier this summer or not, you need to fill out our complete enrollment packet, which is available online now on our website at www.okeene.k12.ok.us under our ‚ÄúEnrollment Forms‚Äù tab, or you can enroll in-person (please wear a mask) at the Pre-K building between 12:00 pm and 5:00 pm tomorrow, which would be Wednesday, July 22nd.
Whether you enroll your student online or in-person, we will also need copies of your child‚Äôs birth certificate, social security card, and immunization record. You can turn in those forms with your enrollment packet tomorrow or you can bring them to the Elementary office. We will need to have those forms before your child can attend our school.

post_text:
2020 Yearbook Information:
The Kansas City Plant closed in March and did not reopen until the middle of May. Production was delayed because of this. The 2020 yearbooks will be distributed on the first day of school, August 13. We do not know if we will be able to have a signing event in the gym lobby because of social distancing requirements. If we cannot meet in the lobby, you will be given time in class to sign the yearbooks. 2020 Seniors who have purchased a yearbook will have two options:

1) You may come to the main entrance of the school the week of August 10-14 and we will bring your yearbook to you.
2) You may leave it here and Mrs. Boeckman will hand it out to be signed by the students. You may then pick it up after that date. If you would like to do this option, please email Mrs. Boeckman and let her know.

There are a limited number of yearbooks left to sell. They will be sold on a first come first serve basis. If you would like to purchase a 2020 yearbook, please email Cheryl Boeckman at cboeckman@okeene.k12.ok.us

If your student was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma‚Äôs Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income.

The application must be submitted prior to the ùêâùêîùêçùêÑ 30ùêìùêá, 2020 deadline at https://secure.okcollegestart.org/applications/Oklahoma_Promise/apply.html. post_text: Just a reminder to everyone that tomorrow, Wednesday, May 6th, will be our final day for serving breakfast and lunches to our students as we are scheduled to end our school year on Friday, May 8th. As usual with your Wednesday pick-up, you will receive breakfast and lunch materials for both Thursday and Friday. We would like to thank Keystone Food Supply, along with Ginny Unruh for their valiant effort in serving the students of our community during these unprecedented times. We hope this service has served its intended purpose of providing meal opportunities for numerous children here in Okeene.

post_text:
Okeene April 9th Board Meeting Changes:
We are fortunate enough to have some very tech savvy individuals on staff who are going to video the board meeting and live stream it out to the classrooms around the circle of the Jr/Sr high building. We will maintain the CDC limitations of only 10 individuals per room at any given time and will allow for each individual to sit a minimum of 6 feet apart. Those wishing to address the board of education will be called out of the respective classrooms by a member of our administration and taken into the board room to address the board. This process will continue until all those speaking have finished. At the conclusion of the meeting, administrators will assist those in the building with exiting in a safe and timely fashion.

If you have a minute, take a few minutes to click this link to watch this video provided courtesy of Josten's. It's a new Harbor special release from Mike Smith titled ‚ÄúRooted in Love‚Äù, which acknowledges the challenges of this moment and calls for building community and taking care of each other. It is a powerful statement for students, teachers and parents about finding the common threads in what we all are feeling, and using those threads to connect with each other even as we are separating ourselves. Thank you, Jostens.

All Junior High & High School Parents,

We're asking you to take a minute to fill out this survey on home internet access. Please fill out one for every child you have in the Junior High or High School by Thursday, March 26th. This will help us as we begin to plan for distance learning. We want to provide every student with the best resources and access to education we can. We appreciate your support and willingness to work with us during this transition time. Please share and communicate this with others who have students in school!

If you have any trouble filling out the survey, feel free to email your response to lcoleman@okeene.k12.ok.us

post_text: Last week, there was a ground breaking ceremony where the new gymnasium and bus barn will be built out at the sports complex.
